                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a watchman . The prosecutor gave me charge of the prisoners. I saw Thomas drop the pocket-book, as she was going to the watch-house .</p>
               <p>(They were produced in court, and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>THOMAS's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>The money is my property. I never saw the pocket-book till I saw it in the man's hand. I think I saw one in his pocket: he dropped it in the coach, and the other girl picked it up.</p>
               <p>ROBERTS's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>THOMAS <rs id="t17820703-44-verdict182" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17820703-44-verdict182" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
